  "prompt": "What are some of the best stories about Virender Sehwag?",
  "response": "Virender Sehwag, known for his explosive batting and straightforward demeanor, has been involved in many memorable and amusing incidents throughout his cricket career. Here are some of the best stories about him:\n\n1. **No Helmet Six**: Sehwag was known for his fearless batting, and this extended to his mindset on the field. Once, when batting against Andrew Nel of South Africa, Nel was sledging Sehwag, trying to unsettle him by questioning his courage. In response, Sehwag hit the next ball for a six, and famously quipped, \"That's courage for you.\"\n\n2. **Sachin's Century**: During a test match against Sri Lanka in 2008, Sachin Tendulkar was nearing another century. Tendulkar was on 99 when Sehwag, despite instructions to play cautiously, hit a six. When asked why he had taken such a risk when Tendulkar was so close to a milestone, Sehwag reportedly said, \"I was trying to bring the field up so you can score your hundred.\"\n\n3. **Kings XI Punjab Captaincy**: In an IPL match, while leading Kings XI Punjab, Sehwag famously decided to bring himself into the attack. Gulzar Inder Singh Chahal, Sehwag's co-commentator, mentioned Sehwag asked the crowd if he should bowl himself, which the crowd enthusiastically supported.\n\n4. **The \"Baap Baap Hota Hai\" Incident**: In a match against Pakistan, bowler Shoaib Akhtar kept telling Sehwag to hit a six. When Sachin Tendulkar came to the crease, Sehwag reportedly said to Shoaib, \u201cBaap baap hota hai, beta beta hota hai\u201d (Father is always the father, son\u2019s always the son). This became one of cricket's most famous sledging stories.\n\n5. **Singing to Relax**: Sehwag had a unique way of keeping calm at the crease \u2013 he would sing. During his historic triple-century against South Africa, he sang Bollywood songs between deliveries. This habit was a part of his relaxed approach to batting and indicated his comfort in dealing with high-pressure situations.\n\n6. **The 'Joke Gift'**: Sehwag once revealed how teammates celebrated Harbhajan Singh's birthday by giving him a gift box with nothing but a potato inside it. This prank reflected the camaraderie and humor that Sehwag brought to the team environment.\n\nThese stories encapsulate Sehwag's personality both on and off the field \u2013 confident, carefree, and always maintaining a sense of humor. His approach to the game and memorable antics have made him one of cricket's most beloved characters.",
